for hundreds of years SL dogs have save[d] the lives of travellers crossing the dangerous path[pass]
these friendly dogs which were first brought from asia were used as watchdogs even in bromen[roman] times
now that the tenl[tunnle] has been built through the mountains the path[pass] was[is] less dangerous
but each year the dogs are still sent out into the snow whenever a traveller is in difficuty[difficulty]
dispite the new temnl[tunnel] there are still a few peaple who rushly[rashlly] attempt to across the  path[pass] on foot
during the summer mouth[s],the monastery is very busy,for it is visited for[by] thousands of peaple who pass[cross] the path[pass] in cars
as there are so many peaple about the dogs have to be keept[kept] in a special in closure[enclosure]
in winter however life in the monastery is quite diffrent
the tempreture[temperature] drops to minner[-] 30 and very few peaple attemp to cross the path[pass]
the monks prefer winter to summer for they have more privice[privacy]
the drogs have greater freedon[m] too,for they are allowed to wounder[wander] outside their enclosure
